ğŸ› ï¸ Step-by-Step Setup
ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Configure AWS CLI
bash
Copy
Edit
aws configure
Enter:

AWS Access Key ID

Secret Access Key

Default region (e.g., us-east-1)

ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Create a Terraform File (main.tf)
hcl
Copy
Edit
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket" "static_site" {
  bucket = "suhani-static-site-demo"
  acl    = "public-read"

  website {
    index_document = "index.html"
    error_document = "error.html"
  }
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket_object" "index" {
  bucket = aws_s3_bucket.static_site.id
  key    = "index.html"
  source = "index.html"
  acl    = "public-read"
  content_type = "text/html"
}
ğŸ”¸ Make sure index.html file is in the same folder.

ğŸ”¹ Step 3: Initialize Terraform
bash
Copy
Edit
terraform init
ğŸ‘‰ This sets up Terraform in your folder.

ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Apply Your Changes (Deploy)
bash
Copy
Edit
terraform apply
Confirm with yes when it asks.

Terraform will:

Create the S3 bucket

Upload your HTML file

Configure it as a website

ğŸ”¹ Step 5: Access the Website
